{"serial": "62064", "department_serial": 57, "code": "GP5037", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Marine chemistry", "ch": "海洋化學"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "大二、大三、大四同學可選修"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chuang, Pei-Chuan"], "ch": ["莊佩涓"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["5", "6"]}, "loc": {"building": "S", "room": "218"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "地球科學學系", "en": "Department of Geophysics"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 3, "selected": 14, "remark": {"ch": "大二、大三、大四同學可選修", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "學生將學習並掌握海洋化學中的關鍵海洋過程，探討生物、地質和物理因素如何影響和控制海洋化學。他們將熟悉相關的化學、生物、地質和物理術語，並理解海洋化學在不同時間尺度上的變化。此外，學生還將研究海洋在全球物質循環中的重要性。通過本課程，學生將獲得必要的知識和分析技能，能夠從全球角度來研究海洋化學，使他們成為訓練有素的年輕海洋科學家。", "en": "Students will gain a comprehensive understanding of key marine processes in ocean chemistry, investigating how biological, geological, and physical factors influence and regulate these processes. They will familiarize themselves with relevant chemical, biological, geological, and physical terminology and grasp how ocean chemistry varies across different timescales. Moreover, students will explore the oceans‘ role in global material cycles. By completing this course, students will acquire essential knowledge and analytical skills to study ocean chemistry from a global viewpoint, equipping them to become proficient young marine scientists."}, "outline": {"ch": "海洋與大氣、生物圈和岩石圈的交互作用下，幾乎所有元素在其循環中的某個階段都會經過海洋。本課程將介紹發生在海洋內部的主要作用，以及這些作用如何影響海洋的化學性質。學生將了解控制海水中化學物質的分佈原因、不同元素在海洋中平均停留多長時間、海洋化學反應如何與海洋中的生物、地質和物理作用相互影響、海洋的化學性質如何影響地球未來。建議學生具備普通化學以及海洋學概論背景知識。", "en": "Under the interactions with the atmosphere, biosphere, and lithosphere, virtually all elements pass through the ocean at some stage in their cycles. This course will introduce the main processes that occur within the ocean and how these processes affect the ocean‘s chemical properties. Students will learn about the factors controlling the distribution of chemical substances in seawater, how long different elements typically remain in the ocean, how oceanic chemical reactions interact with biological, geological, and physical processes within the ocean, and how the ocean‘s chemical properties can affect the past, present, and future of planet Earth. It is recommended that students have backgrounds in general chemistry and an introduction to oceanography."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Emerson and Hedges: Chemical Oceanography and the Marine Carbon Cycle\n(Cambridge University Press).", "en": "Emerson and Hedges: Chemical Oceanography and the Marine Carbon Cycle\n(Cambridge University Press)."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "90", "en": "90"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n實習/實驗", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "Practical Training Lab"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "期中課堂報告: 30％\n期末課堂報告: 30％\n課堂表現與作業: 40％", "en": "Midterm presentation 30％\nFinal presentation: 30％\nClass participation and assignments: 40％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期四  10:00-12:00", "en": "Thursday  10:00-12:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "文獻回顧", "en": "Literature review"}, "domain": {"ch": "地質\n\n\n、\n\n\n應用地質", "en": "地質\n\n\n、\n\n\n應用地質"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "獨立思考", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "創新研究", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "組織領導", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "國際交流", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Independent thinking", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)", "Practices/Experiments"]}, {"competencies": "Innovative research", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Re